%S A397240 0,0,1,0,0,1,1,1,5,5,15,29,81,181
%N A397240 Number of free ouroboros polyiamonds with 2*n cells.
%C A397240 In analogy with the definition in A359706, an ouroboros polyiamond is a polyiamond in which every cell has exactly two neighbors.
%C A397240 There are no ouroboros polyiamonds with an odd number of cells.
%H A397240 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A397240/a397240.svg">Illustration of all ouroboros polyiamonds with at most 22 cells</a>.
%F A397240 a(n) = A000577(2*n) - A151518(2*n) - A395331(2*n).
%Y A397240 Cf. A000577, A151518, A359706, A395331.
%K A397240 nonn,more,new
%O A397240 1,9
%A A397240 _Pontus von Brömssen_, Jun 19 2026
